---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { AFFILIATE_DISCLOSURE, SITE } from '../lib/site';
---

<Layout
  title="About"
  description="HotPick Lab helps US shoppers and creators keep up with trending products — curated guides and free tools, updated weekly."
  keywords={['about hotpick lab', 'trending product guides', 'honest product picks']}
>
  <article class="prose about-page">
    <h1>About {SITE.name}</h1>
    <p class="about-lead">
      We help you keep up with what's trending — and decide what's actually worth buying.
    </p>

    <h2>What we do</h2>
    <p>
      {SITE.name} publishes <strong>hotspot buying guides</strong> for the US market: AI tools, viral Amazon
      products, gaming gear, and seasonal deals. Each guide includes who it's for, who should skip it, honest
      pros and cons, and a short list of top picks.
    </p>
    <p>
      We also build <strong>free browser tools</strong> — small calculators you can bookmark and use anytime,
      without reading an article first.
    </p>

    <h2>Who it's for</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Shoppers tired of TikTok hype who want a quick reality check</li>
      <li>Creators comparing AI tools, gear, or accessories</li>
      <li>Anyone who wants a short, current answer — not a 3,000-word SEO essay</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 id="how-we-pick">How we pick trends</h2>
    <p>Every week we scan signals from the US market — rising searches, viral products, and real buyer discussions — then ask:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Is interest still climbing, or already fading?</li>
      <li>Can we give a useful answer in one page — who it's for, pitfalls, and top picks?</li>
      <li>Would we honestly recommend skipping some options?</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      If we can't add clarity, we don't publish. Guides are updated when products, prices, or hype shift —
      not left to rot with outdated picks.
    </p>

    <h2>Our tools</h2>
    <p>
      Each tool has its own page you can bookmark or add to your home screen. Guides link to tools when
      they're helpful in context — but tools work on their own, anytime.
    </p>
    <p><a href="/tools">Browse free tools →</a></p>

    <h2>Transparency</h2>
    <p>{AFFILIATE_DISCLOSURE}</p>
    <p>
      <a href="/disclosure">Full affiliate disclosure →</a> ·
      <a href="/privacy">Privacy policy →</a>
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions or corrections? Email <a href={`mailto:${SITE.contactEmail}`}>{SITE.contactEmail}</a>
    </p>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  .about-lead {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: #d9e2ff;
    max-width: 40rem;
  }
</style>
